urope's largest indoor arena\", \"from\": 1464, \"to\": 1493}]}, {\"sentence\": \"McEvoy knew it was where a drop-in pool would be placed for the Olympics.\", \"from\": 1496, \"to\": 1569, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"McEvoy\", \"from\": 1496, \"to\": 1502}, {\"ngram\": \"a drop-in pool\", \"from\": 1521, \"to\": 1535}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 1556, \"to\": 1568}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And he knew, at that drive-by moment, he wanted to swim again.\", \"from\": 1571, \"to\": 1633, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"that drive-by moment\", \"from\": 1587, \"to\": 1607}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"That was the day that I went all in,\\\" McEvoy said.\", \"from\": 1635, \"to\": 1686, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the day\", \"from\": 1645, \"to\": 1652}, {\"ngram\": \"McEvoy\", \"from\": 1674, \"to\": 1680}]}, {\"sentence\": \"All in meant ditching traditional training for the sprint freestyles which McEvoy experienced since his Olympic debut in London a dozen years ago.\", \"from\": 1688, \"to\": 1834, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1809, \"end\": 1815, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999999976221261, \"rank\": 2.374399046964915e-09, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"traditional training\", \"from\": 1710, \"to\": 1730}, {\"ngram\": \"the sprint freestyles\", \"from\": 1735, \"to\": 1756}, {\"ngram\": \"McEvoy\", \"from\": 1763, \"to\": 1769}, {\"ngram\": \"his Olympic debut\", \"from\": 1788, \"to\": 1805}]}, {\"sentence\": \"McEvoy is nicknamed The Professor - he studies phsyics and maths, wants to be an astronaut, and has previously raced with what most thought were sound waves emblazoned on his swim cap.\", \"from\": 1836, \"to\": 2020, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"McEvoy\", \"from\": 1836, \"to\": 1842}, {\"ngram\": \"The Professor\", \"from\": 1856, \"to\": 1869}, {\"ngram\": \"phsyics\", \"from\": 1883, \"to\": 1890}, {\"ngram\": \"maths\", \"from\": 1895, \"to\": 1900}, {\"ngram\": \"an astronaut\", \"from\": 1914, \"to\": 1926}, {\"ngram\": \"sound waves\", \"from\": 1981, \"to\": 1992}, {\"ngram\": \"his swim cap\", \"from\": 2007, \"to\": 2019}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In fact, they were gravitational waves in a nod to Einstein's general theory of relativity which, in part and in layman terms, covers the stretching and contraction of space-time.\", \"from\": 2022, \"to\": 2201, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2073, \"end\": 2081, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Albert_Einstein\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 4.212746867594728e-13, \"text\": \"Einstein\", \"types\": [\"Q901\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Albert_Einstein\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Albert_Einstein\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"fact\", \"from\": 2025, \"to\": 2029}, {\"ngram\": \"gravitational waves\", \"from\": 2041, \"to\": 2060}, {\"ngram\": \"a nod\", \"from\": 2064, \"to\": 2069}, {\"ngram\": \"relativity\", \"from\": 2102, \"to\": 2112}, {\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 2123, \"to\": 2127}, {\"ngram\": \"layman terms\", \"from\": 2135, \"to\": 2147}, {\"ngram\": \"the stretching\", \"from\": 2156, \"to\": 2170}, {\"ngram\": \"contraction\", \"from\": 2175, \"to\": 2186}, {\"ngram\": \"space-time\", \"from\": 2190, \"to\": 2200}]}, {\"sentence\": \"McEvoy returned to the pool, shunning age-old methods in favour of a new-age hunch: there was a better way.\", \"from\": 2203, \"to\": 2310, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"McEvoy\", \"from\": 2203, \"to\": 2209}, {\"ngram\": \"the pool\", \"from\": 2222, \"to\": 2230}, {\"ngram\": \"age-old methods\", \"from\": 2241, \"to\": 2256}, {\"ngram\": \"favour\", \"from\": 2260, \"to\": 2266}, {\"ngram\": \"a new-age hunch\", 